**[MEDIUM] `dmatrix/src/lib.rs`:Line 58 – Inefficient matrix build from columns.**
The `Builder::build` method constructs an `ndarray::Array2` (which is row-major by default) by iterating through columns and then rows. This leads to non-contiguous memory access, which can be slow due to cache misses.

→ **Fix:** Since your data is stored column-wise, flatten it and construct a column-major `ndarray::Array2` using `Array2::from_shape_vec` with a Fortran/column-major layout (`.f()`). This is significantly more efficient.

